data.text:
William vanden Huevel Collection (375), born 1930

William Jacobus vanden Heuvel is an American attorney, businessman and author, as well as a former diplomat. He is the founding chairman of Franklin D. Roosevelt Four Freeoms Park, which was designed by Louis I Kahn.

This collection contains published material about the park, board correpondence, development documents, and general correspondence.
